Akfen Holding, Sinpas GYO: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-06-14T06:38:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/akfen-holding-sinpas-gyo-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 177.08, or
0.3 percent, to 63,523.22 yesterday.  Akfen Holding AS (AKFEN)  : Istanbul Mayor Kadir Topbas
approved the sale of the right to operate the city’s ferry unit
for 30 years for $861 million to a group led by Souter
Investment LLP and Turkish builder Akfen Holding, Zaman said,
without saying where it got the information. Akfen was unchanged
at 11.85 liras.  Sinpas Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS (SNGYO)  : The
Turkish real-estate investment trust signed an agreement with
Turkey’s Rixos hotels to jointly develop, market, lease and
manage luxury apartments, villas and a hotel in Marmaris, a
holiday resort in southwestern Turkey. Sinpas GYO gained 1
kurus, or 0.6 percent, to 1.8 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  